00:14:45.250 --> 00:14:51.540
Okay, so knowing our role and our
function in the end-to-end chain,

00:14:51.540 --> 00:14:56.100
what's the challenges we see and
what challenges do operators see?

00:14:56.100 --> 00:15:02.760
And I think my colleague from Buig
will be discussing their views as well.

00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:07.260
But in our point of view,
there's four main areas that

00:15:07.260 --> 00:15:11.950
are challenges in delivering
mobile media content.

00:15:11.950 --> 00:15:17.200
First and foremost,
it's having the right content and the

00:15:17.200 --> 00:15:20.250
right applications in operator networks.

00:15:20.300 --> 00:15:23.730
It's still not that easy to
find that killer content.

00:15:23.730 --> 00:15:29.070
Then there's the handsets,
the problem of making sure that

00:15:29.090 --> 00:15:32.620
every single content is delivered.

00:15:32.760 --> 00:15:33.760
And then there's the operator networks.

00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:36.310
So we have to be able to integrate
the operator networks into handsets,

00:15:36.310 --> 00:15:38.670
and those handsets can decode and
play the different formats that

00:15:38.670 --> 00:15:40.250
are available in operator networks.

00:15:40.260 --> 00:15:44.630
But apart from that,
we also look at end-to-end integration.

00:15:44.900 --> 00:15:49.350
All right, let's say I have the content
out and my partners are set.

00:15:49.370 --> 00:15:51.240
I have the handsets ready.

00:15:51.540 --> 00:15:56.300
Next thing that the operator asks for,
or the next thing that is asked for,

00:15:56.300 --> 00:15:58.850
is how do I integrate the solution?

00:15:58.860 --> 00:16:01.730
How do I make sure that the
billing interfaces are set,

00:16:01.770 --> 00:16:03.940
that the prepaid interfaces are set?

00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:06.820
How about my integration
to customer care?

00:16:06.950 --> 00:16:10.760
How about my integration
to network management?

00:16:10.840 --> 00:16:15.100
And finally, of course,
there's how should I charge for this?

00:16:15.210 --> 00:16:20.220
And this is still an unknown
area for a lot of operators.

00:16:20.220 --> 00:16:22.260
There's so many ways
you can charge for this.

00:16:22.260 --> 00:16:26.470
It could be subscription-based,
event-based, it could be volume-based,

00:16:26.520 --> 00:16:30.760
it could be category-based,
it could be one-time fee,

00:16:30.780 --> 00:16:34.760
or it could be combined with MMS,
it could be combined with voice.

00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:42.760
There's so many things that could be
possible on a way to charge for this.

00:16:42.760 --> 00:16:48.760
And that is a challenge because this
will actually make or break the service.

00:16:48.760 --> 00:16:50.680
All right, so what's our solution?

00:16:50.880 --> 00:16:52.760
What's Ericsson's solution for this?

00:16:52.760 --> 00:16:56.710
Well, basically,
we have come up with a solution,

00:16:56.770 --> 00:17:01.160
an end-to-end solution that addresses
or aims to address all the content,

00:17:01.170 --> 00:17:05.650
all the relevant formats,
all the relevant protocols,

00:17:05.790 --> 00:17:10.520
connecting that content to the
handsets or the devices that

00:17:10.520 --> 00:17:11.760
will receive that content.

00:17:11.760 --> 00:17:15.610
And what we've done in Ericsson,
or what we focused on Ericsson,

00:17:15.610 --> 00:17:18.760
is the development of a
network integration node.

00:17:18.760 --> 00:17:23.440
And what that does, of course,
is do the integration aspects,

00:17:23.440 --> 00:17:28.680
basically develop features that
bring about our core competencies.

00:17:28.760 --> 00:17:35.750
And what it does is it allows
us to have streaming services.

00:17:35.750 --> 00:17:38.610
Now,
it could be a Sun streaming server or it

00:17:38.610 --> 00:17:40.760
could be a QuickTime streaming server.

00:17:40.760 --> 00:17:44.450
What we want to be,
what we want the system to be is

00:17:44.450 --> 00:17:49.350
agnostic to its streaming server
or streaming platform because we

00:17:49.350 --> 00:17:50.760
want to address the content space.

00:17:50.760 --> 00:17:53.770
So if an operator says,
"I want this type of codec and

00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:57.720
this other streaming server
provides it," then we put that in.

00:17:57.790 --> 00:18:01.730
And I think QuickTime is really
helping us there in terms of

00:18:01.730 --> 00:18:06.680
the new protocols that they're
supporting and 264 is coming up.

00:18:06.830 --> 00:18:11.190
So it could happen that operators
will start asking for that,

00:18:11.190 --> 00:18:13.760
and we will deliver it with that.

00:18:13.860 --> 00:18:18.540
We do also provide content
upload for the content providers,

00:18:18.540 --> 00:18:22.870
content storage rating for that content,
and a subscriber database to

00:18:22.990 --> 00:18:26.730
hold the information about which
services that subscribers want.

00:18:26.760 --> 00:18:35.520
Apart from that, I'd like to explain to
you how our solution,

00:18:35.520 --> 00:18:39.330
which is ECDS,
fits into the radio network

00:18:39.420 --> 00:18:41.760
and the core network.

00:18:41.760 --> 00:18:45.720
The way it works today is we
have support for both circuit

00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:50.310
switch and packet switch,
which is quite a key strength because

00:18:50.310 --> 00:18:55.700
a lot of the existing solutions today
only address the packet switch space.

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:56.760
So we have a lot of different solutions.

00:18:56.820 --> 00:18:57.760
We have a lot of different solutions.

00:18:57.760 --> 00:18:59.750
This is more wireless
technology infrastructure.

00:18:59.830 --> 00:19:03.440
So you have your radio base
stations connected to controllers,

00:19:03.440 --> 00:19:09.010
controllers connected to gateways,
and then finally it's on the Internet or

00:19:09.010 --> 00:19:13.740
within the operator's walled garden.

00:19:13.760 --> 00:19:17.040
And then we have integration
to content creation,

00:19:17.120 --> 00:19:20.740
content management, HLR,
and charging systems.

00:19:20.760 --> 00:19:21.760
Okay?

00:19:21.760 --> 00:19:22.760
So that's the first part.

00:19:24.170 --> 00:19:30.650
So, I told you that one of the
challenges is integration and

00:19:30.660 --> 00:19:32.130
that's why we focus on that.

00:19:32.130 --> 00:19:36.100
We make sure that we have integration
points to the billing gateways,

00:19:36.180 --> 00:19:38.620
we have integration points to
network management systems.

00:19:38.620 --> 00:19:42.540
So, when we talk about network
management systems,

00:19:42.540 --> 00:19:46.260
it could be HP OpenView,
it could be Compact TAMIP,

00:19:46.340 --> 00:19:48.760
