00:40:14.950 --> 00:40:17.740
We made some tests two years ago,
and that was a conclusion

00:40:17.830 --> 00:40:19.390
for 90% of the users.

00:40:20.000 --> 00:40:23.520
When we combine this constraint
with the fact that we have a very

00:40:23.520 --> 00:40:28.600
limited throughput on the network,
we end up with a constraint on the file

00:40:28.600 --> 00:40:31.300
size that is approximately 100 kilobytes.

00:40:31.650 --> 00:40:36.760
And if you look at the table,
then you can see that the

00:40:36.760 --> 00:40:40.680
download duration time on
Edge is approximately between 20,

00:40:40.680 --> 00:40:42.220
30 seconds.

00:40:42.410 --> 00:40:45.500
And the upload duration
is more important.

00:40:45.500 --> 00:40:47.710
It's 80 seconds.

00:40:47.900 --> 00:40:52.560
One thing interesting to see is that
the phones today are not operated

00:40:52.560 --> 00:40:55.040
by a multitask operating system.

00:40:55.110 --> 00:40:58.440
So when I download a
clip from the website,

00:40:58.440 --> 00:41:02.320
well, I wait,
but I can't do anything else.

00:41:03.260 --> 00:41:05.890
If I sent an email with
a video attachment,

00:41:05.890 --> 00:41:06.830
it's the same problem.

00:41:06.990 --> 00:41:10.400
So from a user perspective,
it's very problematic,

00:41:10.400 --> 00:41:12.600
and we have to find some solution.

00:41:12.780 --> 00:41:15.660
And one solution is you
increase the bandwidth,

00:41:15.660 --> 00:41:18.810
so you go to Edge,
and then you have shorter

00:41:18.810 --> 00:41:20.990
upload/download time.

00:41:21.040 --> 00:41:24.380
And that is the way we're going to.

00:41:25.160 --> 00:41:33.350
We also have a problem with video quality
because if we have very small files,

00:41:33.350 --> 00:41:38.270
if we want to have a duration
acceptable that is in the range of 15,

00:41:38.350 --> 00:41:41.470
20 seconds to give the users
a piece of information,

00:41:41.470 --> 00:41:44.800
not only a still image,
then we can't have

00:41:44.800 --> 00:41:47.180
video bitrate very high.

00:41:47.180 --> 00:41:50.700
We are in the range between
32 to 64 kilobits per second.

00:41:50.700 --> 00:41:55.780
I will show you later on what is the
type of quality that we can have on very

00:41:55.780 --> 00:41:58.300
hard content that is on football games,
for instance.

00:42:01.730 --> 00:42:07.440
If we look at video mail services,
it's a service very intuitive

00:42:07.440 --> 00:42:10.260
because it's like an email.

00:42:10.320 --> 00:42:16.510
You just shoot video with your phone,
and then you open the email.

00:42:16.700 --> 00:42:19.420
Email client on the phone,
you put the video as an

00:42:19.420 --> 00:42:21.940
attachment and you sent it.

00:42:22.090 --> 00:42:24.100
Very clever, very simple.

00:42:24.350 --> 00:42:27.120
Or if you have the
authorization to do so,

00:42:27.120 --> 00:42:30.620
if the video that you downloaded
from the web is not a lot,

00:42:30.650 --> 00:42:33.830
then you can forward it to someone else.

00:42:35.660 --> 00:42:39.530
I said iMod is reusing some
technologies existing on the web,

00:42:39.530 --> 00:42:45.540
so what is good with that is that
you can address any email on the web,

00:42:45.540 --> 00:42:46.640
so almost everybody.

00:42:46.640 --> 00:42:50.090
And also you can address
some MMS recipient if you

00:42:50.090 --> 00:42:52.100
have their phone number.

00:42:52.100 --> 00:42:55.860
There is in fact a getaway into the
network that makes some translation

00:42:55.860 --> 00:42:59.850
between the email format and the MMS.

00:43:01.010 --> 00:43:08.240
On the recipient side, well,
you could have different case.

00:43:08.340 --> 00:43:11.520
If it is inside an iMod network,
then it's very easy.

00:43:11.590 --> 00:43:12.960
There is no problem.

00:43:12.970 --> 00:43:16.680
If we talk to an OMS client,
that's what I talked about.

00:43:16.680 --> 00:43:21.100
And if you talk to someone
on a PC on a fixed network,

00:43:21.100 --> 00:43:25.920
then you can look at the video using,
for instance, QuickTime,

00:43:25.920 --> 00:43:28.480
which is very easy to get.

00:43:30.840 --> 00:43:33.090
Video download is the other service.

00:43:33.220 --> 00:43:35.700
So it's HTTP download.

00:43:35.830 --> 00:43:38.260
It has a little overhead
during the transportation,

00:43:38.260 --> 00:43:44.200
so we had to think about that when
we look at how to charge the content.

00:43:44.830 --> 00:43:51.540
And it's very important because
the users pays for transport.

00:43:51.940 --> 00:43:58.400
Here I put different captures
in order to show you the steps.

